On print
FYI when using tok do not call any of the Buffer append directly. use print or cout. Assume buffer exists:
	print(buffer) text;		gets converted by tok into
	buffer->appendString(text,0,0);
	buffer += text			produces the same result. buffer += is type aware so buffer += 42; works the same way
print(buffer) sets the default print output to the buffer instead of stdout. As code is parsed, every subsequent print command will do the same until there is a print command like
	print() whatever…;		the empty parens reset the default printer to stdout

